1
00:00:05,302 --> 00:00:09,372
You’ll have to appreciate
the devotees of Kṛṣṇa,

2
00:00:09,804 --> 00:00:12,990
[Mystery of Kṛṣṇa Conception]

3
00:00:13,220 --> 00:00:17,989
not to think you can have
a direct connection with divinity.

4
00:00:17,989 --> 00:00:20,420
The shift is going to take place,

5
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:24,622
you’re going to understand
the necessity of the devotee,

6
00:00:24,622 --> 00:00:30,063
and the happy necessity
of the devotee.

7
00:00:33,709 --> 00:00:38,823
And of the highest devotee,
Achyuta Priya,

8
00:00:40,683 --> 00:00:44,860
we can say,
Achyuta Priya Paramahaṁsa, that

9
00:00:44,860 --> 00:00:47,900
Kṛṣṇa’s dear 
to the paramahaṁsas;

10
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:50,542
but if we take 
the name Achyuta Priya,

11
00:00:50,542 --> 00:00:55,168
it can also mean
‘who’s most dear to Achyuta’.

12
00:00:55,168 --> 00:01:02,402
The name Achyuta is used
in the Pañchadhyaya section

13
00:01:02,555 --> 00:01:06,124
—five chapters of the rasa-lila
in the Tenth Canto—

14
00:01:09,114 --> 00:01:15,113
so it can also indicate
Śrīmatī Rādhāṛāṇī,

15
00:01:15,843 --> 00:01:19,288
as Guru is most dear to Kṛṣṇa;

16
00:01:19,288 --> 00:01:24,971
Raghunāth Dās Goswāmī says,
“Mukunda-preṣṭhā”.

17
00:01:26,822 --> 00:01:30,629
Of all
who are dear to Kṛṣṇa,

18
00:01:30,629 --> 00:01:36,335
who is the most dear to Kṛṣṇa
means Śrīmatī Rādhāṛāṇī,

19
00:01:36,473 --> 00:01:41,986
so the highest expression
of guru-tattva

20
00:01:42,070 --> 00:01:46,117
is realised in Her.

21
00:01:48,471 --> 00:01:53,130
So, those 
who do not recognise Her,

22
00:01:53,353 --> 00:01:57,221
cannot enter into the mysteries
of Kṛṣṇa conception.

23
00:01:57,251 --> 00:02:00,865
Those who do not recognise Her,
and by extension,

24
00:02:00,865 --> 00:02:05,894
Her delegation, cannot enter
into the mysteries of Kṛṣṇa conception;

25
00:02:05,894 --> 00:02:20,449
at best they can have some remote
isolated concept of Kṛṣṇa.

26
00:02:21,740 --> 00:02:26,547
Vāsudevaḥ sarvam iti sa
mahātmā sudurlabhaḥ (Bg: 7.19).

27
00:02:26,547 --> 00:02:29,561
Vaṣudev, Kṛṣṇa, alone.

28
00:02:29,681 --> 00:02:36,805
But Bhagavān proper is Kṛṣṇa
in the company of His Potency.

29
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:42,169
So, ‘so 'ham’—the ‘saḥ’,
as Guru Mahārāj said,

30
00:02:42,169 --> 00:02:47,099
“What is the nature of He?”

31
00:02:47,146 --> 00:02:53,668
He said, “Like a king”, and king
implies: queen, kingdom, etc.

32
00:02:53,668 --> 00:02:56,652
He said, “But the king
has many positions also:

33
00:02:56,681 --> 00:03:00,655
king in the palace,
king in the harem.

34
00:03:00,691 --> 00:03:04,923
He behaves differently, 
that king.”

